6">Crossref</a></div></div></li><li class="citedByEntry" data-doi="10.1007/s10554-017-1127-x"><div class="related"><div class="related__title"><a target="_blank" href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10554-017-1127-x">Magnetic resonance imaging for characterizing myocardial diseases</a></div><div class="related__authors"><ul class="rlist--inline loa mobile-authors loa-height"><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Maythem Saeed</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Hui Liu</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Chang-Hong Liang</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Mark W. Wilson</span></li></ul></div><div class="meta">31 March 2017 | The International Journal of Cardiovascular Imaging, Vol. 33, No. 9</div></div><div class="getFTR external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10554-017-1127-x">Crossref</a></div></div></li><li class="citedByEntry" data-doi="10.1007/s10554-016-0906-0"><div class="related"><div class="related__title"><a target="_blank" href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10554-016-0906-0">Use of a semi-automated cardiac segmentation tool improves reproducibility and speed of segmentation of contaminated right heart magnetic resonance angiography</a></div><div class="related__authors"><ul class="rlist--inline loa mobile-authors loa-height"><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Animesh Tandon</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Nicholas Byrne</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Maria de las Nieves Velasco Forte</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Song Zhang</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Adrian K. Dyer</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Jeanne M. Dillenbeck</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Gerald F. Greil</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Tarique Hussa